Ans-3. LAN stands for Local Area Network, which is a network that covers a small geographic area, typically within a single building or campus. LANs are often used for connecting devices like computers, printers, and servers within an office, home, or school. They typically use Ethernet or Wi-Fi technology for connectivity and can be set up and managed privately by an organization.\par
