   - Acknowledgment (ACK) is a signal sent by the receiver to the sender to confirm successful receipt of data packets.\par
   - When the sender receives an ACK, it knows that the data was successfully delivered and can proceed to send the next set of data.\par
   - In cases where an ACK is not received, the sender may retransmit the data to ensure its delivery.\par

